 {"id":"bd-7zps","title":"Idea: Last-successful worker fallback","description":"## Background
When selection fails (no matching workers), the system could fall back to the last worker that successfully built this project. This improves resiliency when metadata is stale.

## Goals
- If selection yields no worker, attempt last-successful worker if healthy.
- Keep failure semantics unchanged if fallback also fails.

## Design / Approach
- Track last-successful worker per project in daemon history.
- On selection failure, check fallback worker status/circuit/runtime requirements.
- Record fallback usage in logs.

## Tasks / Subtasks
- Persist last-successful worker mapping.
- Extend selection logic with fallback path.
- Add diagnostics and status visibility.

## Tests
- Unit: fallback logic with unhealthy worker.
- Integration: selection failure triggers fallback if healthy.
- E2E: fallback used when all matching filters exclude workers.

## Acceptance Criteria
- Fallback improves success rate without masking real errors.
- Behavior is transparent in logs/status.

## Logging & E2E
- E2E script: scripts/e2e_bd-7zps.sh (one script per bead unless intentionally combined).
- Logging format: JSONL via TestLogger (tests/true_e2e/logging.rs) or scripts/test_lib.sh log_json.
- Required fields: ts, test, phase, worker, command, bytes_transferred, duration_ms, result, error (if any).
- Phases to log (as applicable): classify, select, sync_up, exec, sync_down, cleanup, summary.
- Include a final summary block with pass/fail counts and total elapsed time.

## Edge Cases & UX
- Fallback only if worker healthy, runtime OK, and slots available.
- Do not override explicit policy failures (e.g., no runtime).
- Log when fallback is used.

## E2E Outline
- Force selection failure -> fallback uses last-success worker.
- Unhealthy fallback -> no selection and clear reason.

## Unit Tests (Detailed)
- rchd/src/selection.rs: fallback logic with health/runtime checks.
- rchd/src/history.rs: last-successful worker retrieval.

## E2E Script Notes
- scripts/e2e_bd-7zps.sh: selection failure -> fallback; unhealthy -> no fallback.
